# Spatial fabric / RP1 publish — protected (do not regress)

**User-confirmed good state (2026-06-19).** Read `memory-bank/spatial-fabric-rp1-protected-state.md` and `docs/SPATIAL_FABRIC_INTEGRATION.md` before editing publish/browser paths.

## Invariants

| Area | Rule |
|------|------|
| Browser URL | Open **Scene Assembler root** (`MSF_PUBLIC_BASE_URL`); **never** navigate to raw `.msf` files |
| TaskManager | `apiEndpoint` from `getApiEndpoint()` only — no duplicate prop |
| Publish | Completed **mesh** jobs → `POST /api/v1/spatial-fabric/publish` on DGX API |
| DGX API | `/api/v1/spatial-fabric/*` routes must be loaded; `.env` MSF vars sourced on restart |
| Naming | OpenNexus3DStudio in product strings; Character Studio = attribution only |
| Secrets | Never commit `.env`, `memory-bank/`, `MONETIZATION_ROADMAP.md`, MSF edit keys |

## Protected files

`spatialFabricAdapter.js`, `useSpatialFabric.js`, `TaskManager.jsx` (publish handler), `GLBExport.jsx`, `WorldLibrary.jsx`, `spatialFabricAdapter.test.js`

## Forbidden without explicit user request

- Opening `fabric_msf_url` / `.msf` as the Metaverse Browser tab URL
- Re-adding `apiEndpoint` prop to TaskManager when `getApiEndpoint()` exists
- Committing moat docs, roadmap, or secrets to git
